Detailed Description

This class implements a simple helper Python type.

Objects of this type are used to represent methods that the client can call on the server.

PyObject * ServerCaller::pyCall ( PyObject *  args  ) 

This method is called with this object is "called" in script.

This is what makes this object a functor. It is responsible for putting the call on the bundle that will be sent to the server.

Parameters:
args A tuple containing the arguments of the call.
Returns:
Py_None on success and NULL on failure. If an error occurs, the Python error string is set.
